+{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_015qvjQ7Sa1o4Ji6zuhTfbkh","type":"tool_result","content":"     1‚Üí# T4: Phantom Invoice Bug\n     2‚Üí\n     3‚Üí**Category:** bugfix/medium\n     4‚Üí**Timeout:** 30 minutes\n     5‚Üí**Diff limit:** 20 changed lines in `src/`\n     6‚Üí\n     7‚Üí## Description\n     8‚Üí\n     9‚ÜíAn invoicing microservice has several failing tests. Your job is to find and fix the bugs so that all tests pass.\n    10‚Üí\n    11‚ÜíRun `npm test` to see the current failures. There are 30 visible tests ‚Äî 4 are currently failing. There is also a hidden regression test suite with 10 tests. Your fix must not break any passing tests.\n    12‚Üí\n    13‚Üí### Constraints\n    14‚Üí\n    15‚Üí- Your changes to `src/` must be at most 20 lines (added + removed), enforced by `tests/diff-size.test.ts`.\n    16‚Üí- Do not modify any test files.\n    17‚Üí- `npm run build` and `npm run lint` must continue to pass.\n    18‚Üí\n    19‚Üí### Hints\n    20‚Üí\n    21‚Üí- The bugs are in the service/query layer, not in the test expectations.\n    22‚Üí- Read the failing test names carefully ‚Äî they describe the expected behavior.\n    23‚Üí- Not every TODO comment or suspicious-looking function is actually a bug that needs fixing.\n    24‚Üí\n    25‚Üí## Getting Started\n    26‚Üí\n    27‚Üí```bash\n    28‚Üínpm install\n    29‚Üínpm test        # See which tests fail\n    30‚Üínpm run build   # Verify TypeScript compiles\n    31‚Üínpm run lint    # Verify lint passes\n    32‚Üí```\n    33‚Üí\n    34‚Üí## Validation\n    35‚Üí\n    36‚ÜíAll 30 visible tests + 10 hidden regression tests must pass. The diff constraint test must also pass.\n    37‚Üí"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01KbRHk5cLN5HLuroTPVG8dw","session_id":"53811a29-0446-4208-afcd-d53aaea285ec","uuid":"98bfea68-eeab-42e2-ba12-80dc23aea526"}
