+{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01LW8yN2aX1am2vo1QknPiDy","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The tests set `TZ = 'America/New_York'`. The reporting code in `getMonthlyReport` does `new Date(inv.date + 'T00:00:00Z')` which creates a UTC date. But then `d.getMonth()` returns the month in local time (America/New_York, UTC-5). So a date like `2024-03-01T00:00:00Z` would be `2024-02-29T19:00:00` in New York, making `getMonth()` return 1 (February) instead of 2 (March).\n\nThis is the timezone bug! The fix: use `getUTCMonth()` instead of `getMonth()`."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1305,"cache_read_input_tokens":30915,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1305},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"53811a29-0446-4208-afcd-d53aaea285ec","uuid":"f76f164b-d60a-4e30-acb2-339fc1c16784"}
